  <h1>
   draw_get_colour
  </h1>
  This function returns the current draw colour which is used for drawing forms, text, primitives and un-textured 3D models. This can be set with the
  <a href="draw_set_colour.htm">
   <span>
    draw_set_colour()
   </span>
  </a>
  function.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_get_colour()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Colour_And_Alpha/Colour_And_Alpha.htm">
 Colour
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var _cur_color = draw_get_color();
draw_set_color(text_color);
draw_text(x, y, text);
draw_set_color(_cur_color);
</code></pre>
  The above code stores the current draw colour into a local variable, and changes the draw colourÂ based on an instance variable. After drawing some text, it resets the colour back to the value stored in the local variable.
